{{otheruses3|Hardwire}}
'''Hardwired''' means "not changeable". It is used in [[technology|technical]] descriptions to denote a lack of any reprogramming/switching/selection mechanisms where there might be room for one. The term is frequently used in the fields of [[electronics]] and [[computer]]s.

The term has moved into popular culture, wherein the same implacability is imputed to groups or individuals.  An individual who is normally perceived as flexible may be described as hardwired in a given situation.  ("It was like he was hardwired: No matter what I said, he wanted that raise!")

In [[human being|human]]s and [[animal]]s, '''hardwired''' refers to [[genetic determinism|genetically determined]], [[instinct|instinctive]] behavior, as opposed to [[learning|learned]] behavior. For example, many [[linguistics|linguists]], including [[Noam Chomsky]], believe that aspects of human [[language]] are hardwired into our brains by [[DNA].].

''See also'': [[hard code|hardcoding]]

